CatDescriptText: Mrs. Carrie Rumph, housewife, 3351 Milwaukee Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 8, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Which of these sources of leadership do you believe Negroes generally follow: church, labor, or politics? Why?" answer reads: "I believe that most Negroes follow church leadership.  And the reason is that people are more often together in church than they are in any other organization.  I think that most people feel that there is stronger leadership in the church.  In my opinion, it is the best."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Carrie Rumph wearing eyeglasses, hat with netting, and gloves, holding paper bag, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
